      <h1 class='title'>Finance Bill</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 22 March 2004 vol 419 c45WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_45ws' title='Col. 45WS &mdash; HC Deb 22 March 2004 vol 419 c45WS' name='column_45ws' href='#column_45ws' rel='bookmark'>45WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0419P2-00497'>
        <a name='S6CV0419P2_20040322_CWS_6'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-dawn-primarolo' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0419P2_20040322_CWS_6' title='Link to this speech by Ms Dawn Primarolo' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-dawn-primarolo" title="Ms Dawn Primarolo">The Paymaster General (Davin Primarolo)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0419P2-00497">As I announced in the debate on the Budget resolutions on 18 March,<span class="italic">Official Report,</span> column 538, the Government intend to publish the <a href="/bills/finance-bill">Finance Bill</a> on Thursday 8 April. Explanatory notes on the Bill's clauses will be available in the Vote Office and the Libraries of both Houses on that day. Members of the public will be able to obtain copies of the explanatory notes from the Treasury. These will also be available on the Treasury's website <span class="underline">http://www.hm-treasury.gov.uk/.</span></p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
